Life is a wonderful journey that takes you far away then surprisingly brings you back to your roots. I got to reconnect with my childhood family for several of their birthdays the other night @ladybyrdcafe We all grew up around Plummer Park in Hollywood off Fountain Ave. Melrose was our backyard from Gardner Elementary & Bancroft J.H.S. to Fairfax High. I feel so blessed to share such real memories with these soulfully rich peeps. Together we experienced the entire cultural movement that birthed in the mid 80’s till the end of the 90’s. I’m so proud of you all, you’ve made families of your own & found success!!! Can’t wait to build with my fam further, you all are such bright shining beautiful people.  #OGs #forever #love #family #friends

The CBS CREW documentary is finally out after years in the making! This film is real special to me, capturing a period in my teenage life growing up graffiti; amazing that we still have footage from back then & of the late greats #SK8ONE #DJROBONE my brothers who brought me in & up. SK8 ONE was a living god, they aren’t made like him anymore. He was a reaction to the social conditions in 1980’s Los Angeles. 6’7” 320lb long blond haired blue eyed skating giant, Aaron Seth Anderson was larger than life to say the least, outsized only by his heart that he gave generously to unite our whole city at times. The graffiti scene was full of big legendary players from all the top crews, but SK8 was a rare breed unto his own, a true living legend. We experienced some real ass life together - running from the cops high on acid, hitting freeway walls, pulling all night bombing missions, having the time of our lives waging a real cultural revolution unlike anything before or since. I miss him to this day. ROB ONE & I went to kindergarten together in Hollywood, he was a cultural magician at a young age working with east coast artists branching hip hop & graffiti for the west coast as if he were a teenage social media celebrity back in 1988. Because Rob had the ins I experienced early club life like the historic Water the Bush with Grandmaster Caz & @princewhipper. Rob & I and about a dozen of us young hungry vandals were originally brought together by SK8 joining the CBS CREW & together we dominated much of Hollywood & surrounding Southern California. Melrose was our central hang spot where we rocked murals up & down the blvd & alleyways. Graffiti was the voice of the dissatisfied soul; living day to day as a permissionless tribe, vandalizing from dawn till dusk, a peaceful reaction to a system that had failed us and that we did not approve of. We were literally trying to change things with our bad ass art, but we were young & life got complicated. Amazingly, someone aka SIME ONE was always there secretly filming. Big ups to the filmmaker, my dear brother @bleek_mayhem for his “Can’t Be Stopped” drive to create this nostalgic film, narrated by @ogeverlast ✊🏼✊🏽✊🏾✊🏿

When I witness @freestylefellowship I’m taken to a place where I feel free from today’s heavy mess. This mesmerizing realness, the authentic essence of something so pure in a time when everything seems disingenuous. Cutting through the thick sickness of modern music malaise is the sound of the mystic speaking clear words of beauty. Heal me from the corporate parasites emitting mind control stupidity over the air waves. The voices of the #InnerCityGriots mixing jazz with the Santa Anas like palm trees swaying to the breeze #FreestyleFellowship transformed the Angelino head state from a knuckle dragging, impulse responding teenager into a realm of sudden wisdom. The lyrical styles of @aceyalone @myka9 @abbeyrizzle migrate the soul toward a converging time of revelations, evolution, elevation, where earlier spiritual music was re-ciphered into a condensed form of human magic called the LA underground. Their music encapsulates an organic consciousness from a time where substance & resistance to commercialism & consumerism birthed much of the counterculture we experience today. Much love to my @projectblowedla fam & its queen @legendmedusa ✊🏿✊🏾✊🏽✊🏼

I’ve been submerging my mind into the Rosicrucian recently after a hiatus of what seems like 30 years, reconstructing a gnosis in alchemy. The most compelling aspect to what I’m studying is there is nothing new under the sun, only forgotten factors that make our universe work. Transformation of one’s consciousness is the reason for science and the powers that be are quite versed with this idea. The problem is they’re  not interested in it. A life in pursuit of escapism leads to boredom, this being a common problem for those who don’t understand the laws of nature. If the pursuit of happiness is based in controlling other people’s power, then one has lost their soul and become a deranged version of man, twisted, obsessing over more power. This all reflects heavy upon our current condition and quality of life. The parasitical behavior of those who desire authority over others - from politicians to teachers, doctors to lawyers, institutions and corporations - is clear, they are in a state of denial over the purpose of life and no longer have the reason to be in control. Rather, we already had the answers over 100 years ago. We just need to re-evaluate our position in this reality and make a choice to evolve on our own free will. If we are to advance forward we’ll need to rethink what is going on here and command those who demand our trust to step down. No higher authority than the laws of nature. We are all nature, we must wake up and live in accordance with this realization. Full vid/credit: https://youtu.be/kVNs6VlMtAk

The art of resistance runs synonymous with outliers, those who help pull the veil of secrecy back in order to wake people from their corporate-induced slumber. When we find ourselves feeling powerless in the face of the enormity of corporate control is where we find a thriving counterculture and a powerful response by those who resist complacency. We are bound by a universal predicament, we are not simple consumers, our voice calls out through the current zeitgeist to use their power against them, a kind of icon-aikido. You can fight fire with fire as long as your flame is hotter, and this inversion we feel can be used against the psychopathology of the ruling corporate elites. The biblical mythos and fuel of subliminal conspiracies has manifest its influence in the Mark of The Beast. Artist Brandy Flower has turned it back on those who would market mindlessness through toxic products and rhetoric, the Mark of The Beast dialectic counters with wit. How utterly aggravated these corporate charlatans must feel when their nefarious concoctions find their way back home, rearranged with the intent to dislodge these psychological parasites from our unconsciousness. The use of reappropriation holds a negative connotation only as long as it steals from authenticity, but when turned against these charlatans, like an anagram, it rearranges the way we see something. This is how to invert the inverted. Go cop @marksofthebeast newest publication with foreward by me over on their page ✊🏼✊🏽✊🏾✊🏿

MYKA 9 hands down is one of the greats! I’m honored to know him & have collaborated with the king & @freestylefellowship since the early 90’s. This is his newest book of poetry, pure genius. For over 3 decades he’s been sharing his path from Los Angeles as an evolved amalgamation, a hybrid spitting endless chops of intellect & wisdom like some Zulu samurai outlaw slaying the competition. Able to touch the light & express its radiance my man is like Prometheus! The magic of his mastery is experienced through reading his work. What stands out for me above all is MYKA is a self-instrument, his rhythm & cadence as well his musical tone make him multi-faceted like a human clarinet. Who remembers when @myka9 @aceyalone @abbeyrizzle @busdriverr battled Wu-Tang on Power 106’s Wake Up Show. That was a moment for all hip-hop heads, the shit was lit! From the trenches of the late 80’s to the cerebral reality of now my man is still way ahead of his time. One of your biggest fans right here “Hoo Huh”! Shout out to @parker_pubs go cop this special edition paperback with my cover art over on his page. #myka9 #freestylefellowship #grammynominated

Whenever you feel lost, sick, overwhelmed with your personal struggles in life take note, it is not a sign that you are about to experience a collapse. It is just a reminder manifesting in your daily life that your spiritual life has been neglected. In this painting I am illustrating the wounded healer‘s self-prognosis and navigational instruments that we are equipped with to realign us to our divinity. 

1. Plan to address your stress & fear with an openness to learn & grow, in a meditative space in communion with Mother Nature.
2. In this plan pull from the moon & stars, use the elements of fire & water out in the open air. 
3. Removal of shoes to ground with the Earth. 
4. Consume the food of the Gods & speak to Her. Can you hear Her in the babbling brook, she sees you, can you see the Owl? 
5. Make an offering to engage the Phoenix Cycle. 
6. In order to initiate this blessing you must be ready for astral travel in order to be present with Her. 

Before you can engage these worlds you will be visited by life forms preparing your subconscious for this journey. Many aspects of yourself will be divulged & digested in order to grow from their purpose. Temptations of social superficial realism designed in our mind attempt to distract, until meditative powers find you ready to blast off into infinity. This library of mind, body & soul, the Akashic Records electric in nature is your evolved, expanded body spanning infinitely as you are God in this state of consciousness. As above so below, every part contains the whole. Perfection completely realized in the geometry of God and self as other is one. Magnetism is the purpose. Man & Woman, Electric ⚡️ Magnetic 🧲 Love ❤️ fractals of self-realization pulsating in every beat of the heart. Cosmic consciousness introduced by the ancestral undulation transportation back into your physical body. Now you are sound, on new found ground at play with the space between reality, softly drifting back to physical. #amidsummernightstrip #metaphysicalsurrealism

I see us as nothing more than the highest form of consciousness this planet has yet to produce. We are like these hair follicle antennas reaching into the electrics here, downloading data transcribing into reality. This beautiful sentient relationship waiting for your participation is what our lives were granted for. Every generation takes a piece from its predecessor & destroys much of the rest in order to rebuild it, adding that piece to a long chain of evolution in the consciousness that we all share. This action is a state of bliss when achieved & it brings functionality, meaning & purpose to our core being. Emptying of the mind is key in order to see beyond the physical realm. It seems that reality is nothing more than a projection of our thoughts. Time is required for us to gather the elements needed to bring thought into three-dimensional form. Everything from the chair to computer is a manifestation derived from the mind. Where did these thoughts come from? Were they our own or are we just in a puzzle of ourselves transcribing transcriptions? Mythology is reality as is magic is language, we speak things into being calling out words like casting a spell to perform magic. These things are not taught to us in school because we would become unruly. Rather they have us be ruled in a technological mechanized reality of AI, a world inverted obsessed with division, disorder, destruction; our submission will be our demise through all that we create & worship. But these authority figures, be they man or machine, are unnecessary obstacles that we must overcome evolving humanity towards its destiny, not its fate. We are in flow now with the Aquarian age, a spiritual time where the middleman is no longer necessary to connect you to the source of all. Some call the source God, Yahweh, Allah, Indra, it really doesn’t matter what name you subscribe to, what matters is the state of consciousness you exist within. The honoring of all humans, the respect for individual thoughts, the willingness to communicate with others in order to harmonize are all part of our nature & we are real AF! “The Pool of Akashic Records” on view @tripoligallery #metaphysicalsurrealism
More install pics of “A Star Is Born” @tripoligallery ✨ All points in time and space are connected ✨ #tripoligallery #apaleolithicage #metaphysicalsurrealism

Who was under the 1ST ST. BRIDGE back in the early to mid-2000’s?! There were circles of culture colliding under the bridge those nights. This was the classic “underground” reminiscent of the late 1980’s scene before they became raves. Elements from all the collectives in Los Angeles gave me an opportunity to rock live art with spray paint bringing my graffiti to the concrete stage. This "Ascension" character was a consistent image from my early art shows representing the innercity awakening of the conscious individual - "Graffiti is the voice of the dissatisfied soul!" These were such rich cultural manifestations we all took part in & I feel so blessed to have played a participating role. I wonder what it will take to bring everyone back together like that. I know everyone is still doing their work, but to synergise again is long overdue. A lot of change is headed our way and my message has stayed its course. Consciousness is a kind of non-physical muscle designed to cut through the ILLogic & confusion we are fed. From time immemorial we’ve had this peripheral view of divinity, but are so distracted by politics that we live in contradictions by our unconscious acts rendering us remote controlled. There is deep hidden gnosis embedded in each of us waiting for the switch to be turned on. The answers lie beyond plastic trash & digital hypnosis, they can be found in the motives of our adversaries and the dark energy that had them sleep so deep they awoke inverted, initiating the mindset of the new popular. Opaque gelatinous toxic formless thinking, smug above the rest & convinced of its own virtue denying all other potentials based on mathematical precision in a vacuum. This neo-narcissist mythical antichrist atheist gordian knot of the technocrats is currently taking over the natural world. Many of us are completely unaware of what is coming down the pipelines & a constant state of awakening is necessary to stay focused on what’s really happening. Only in community can we share this common goal, cleansing each other's psyches through the work we do so that we might see clearly and choose freedom over slavery ✊🏼✊🏽✊🏾✊🏿

Throwin it back a hot minute to Miami, 2012. This mural was a crazy whirlwind experience completed in 2 1/2 days, over 100’ long & 25’ high, yeah I must have been high lol. I’m kinda crazy because much of what I did back then was freestyle & freehand. This mural could have lent itself to stencil work, but for one reason or another I skipped the presets & jumped right into spraypainting, bringing the synthesis of my thinking to play on this wall during Art Basel. The priming was done by my bro @riskrock the mad man on a lift! He was busy painting multiple buildings while I worked on this one, which was covered on every side by a different team. The whole neighborhood was getting rocked, what a great time, sunshine heat & all night painting half-naked in paradise. All praise to the electromagnetic substructure making everything possible! My fascination with these laws of nature fill my soul with purpose & meaning. My drive is powered by the dynamo flow of wake up, eat breakfast, smoke a fatty & go!!! See you in May Miami, then again in November for a surprise @museumofgraffiti gonna be choppin it up with them live at 4PM PST today here, tune in 📡 beats by @nosajthing “eclipse/blue” ✊🏼✊🏽✊🏾✊🏿

This is some #wildassshit from the days of ditching & tagging. Made it into the official mainstream like a Trojan horse full of surprises. A legacy pioneered in Los Angeles by my brothers & I, the “OG Can’t Be Stopped Crew.” Big ups to my man @bleek_mayhem writer & director of this historic documentary about brotherhood, graffiti and cultivating LA underground culture. #cantbestopped streaming now ✊🏼✊🏽✊🏾✊🏿

Spending some time with the ol’ pen & ink here, bringing the sacred mythos to our zeitgeist. Annual cycles of change teach a deeper meaning in life. Being a Scorpio the Phoenix holds significant meaning to me. This bird of fire has within its grasp its serpent nemesis, the ouroboros, suggesting revolutions of immorality as well reincarnation. Throughout much of antiquity we find the Raptor & Serpent locked in a cosmic battle. This symbology is the substructure of our psychological & physiological makeup, cycles that confront us when we least expect them. Our lives at times can be a rollercoaster, derailing or empowering, it changes us & we find ourselves reborn fresh with new perspectives. I will be bringing this illustration to silkscreen soon, more to come. #phoenixcycle #immortality #metaphysicalsurrealism

It’s all a big shit show 💩 I was painting this absurd reality back in the days, I could see it coming & now here we are. As AI takes out the workforce transforming our natural order to calculated organization, rest assured that when the fart dust clears you will own nothing & be completely happy. Is this the future you signed up for?

When @illb1ll from NON PHIXION came by my studio in 2002 I was working on this post-911 mad max piece that ended up being the cover art for his seminal LP, THE FUTURE IS NOW. I was on a war path fighting for my freedom of expression & critical mind, art was my weapon & armageddon was knocking at the door. We became a country in lockstep with the homeland hostage authorities dictating subjugation & fear propaganda live at 5. This was my response, a flaming middle finger shining a spotlight on the circus that runs the whole show. It’s one of my favorite album covers I’ve painted over the years & I’m pumped to see the homie keeping real Hip-Hop alive during these unveiling times, celebrating the culture with this 20th anniversary special edition pressing, preorder link in @illb1ll @unclehowie @fatbeats bio/bestseller. #thefutureisnow ⚡️✊🏼✊🏽✊🏾✊🏿⚡️

In these turbulent times our connection with Mother Earth is crucial to avoid being wrapped up in society’s madness. Spiritual thought has been corrupted for centuries by governments, allowing them to control what we think. They act as a middle man blocking any natural interpretation or personal experience. If we follow this path we will succeed in constructing a despotic nightmare, and this is where we find ourselves - devoid of unity, consumed by nihilism, society has never been so disconnected. Yet my angst toward authority becomes irrelevant in the presence of earth changes, producing a very real geological transformation. This idea connects me to catastrophism, the origins and mythology of God Worship, and the reason belief systems ever developed in the first place. Nature, a simplex manifestation of intelligent design produces our existence; these changes come sudden and unannounced evolving life time again. Stop and take notice of the still present wild and what is left of the natural world, feel her magnetic energy pull you home to who you were before the system corrupted our reality. We are the cosmos experiencing ourselves together in order to fulfill a feedback loop of pattern evolving through consciousness and process. At its core, this new earth vision of humanity celebrates a spiritual rite that supersedes the dictations of authority. The origin of belief, that which breathes air into your existence, the light of life and spirit, the mother of invention and caretaker of our reality, coming soon. #motherearth #earthday #illustration #silkscreen

I’m here in Tahoe creating a fresco for my good friends @tahoewellness beautiful new expansion. This high plains vision will be the centerpiece for their grand opening this Thursday, let the countdown to 4/20 begin!!! For the love of Mother Nature & the new evolution of this great institute, more to come✌️💨💨💨
Making progress on this 55’ x 5’ fresco, the planets are aligned here @tahoewellness for Mother Earth to come through and help anchor the soul of humanity. #earthpeople

Jamming on this telluric theme of celestial consciousness with my fam @tahoewellness Mother Earth is a major theme in my work. I’ve climbed many mountains, made my way through deep canyons & slept under great trees in search of God. In my quest I’ve wondered, where is this God? It has taken me a lifetime of letting go of bad ideas, clearing my inner path in order to witness the universe manifest its truth in a form I can understand & recognize. God for me is the process of receiving information. This invisible stream of consciousness communicating the relevance of being. This omnipotent presence of a process operating outside of our control, yet existing within everyone of us. Every question I’ve ever searched becomes realized when I sit in silence & observe Mother Nature present an answer that is beyond simple truth, it penetrates across the board healing any other issues unknown or unseen. The magic of nature is that it breaks our dependency upon authoritative ideologies. The involuntary actions that keep you alive are the design of intelligence beyond our own. After all the charlatans have tried to manipulate you through false religions; the truth of nature will embrace you & make you whole again.

8 days in on the most detailed 5x55’ acrylic installation I’ve ever painted here @tahoewellness There’s no better place to express the love & respect for nature. I take my breaks, step out the door & I’m continually stunned by this little town hugging the lake surrounded by the beautiful sierras covered in glaciers. Blessed to share these high frequency vibes here with my Tahoe family.

A belated Mother’s Day gift for all my mamma bears out there ✊🏼✊🏽✊🏾✊🏿 The center piece of my latest fresco is dedicated to Mother Earth who sees all that the world once was, is, and could be. We are the custodians of nature and we can have a paradise if we want it. Take responsibility for the world around you, make it better, leave more beauty than ugliness. Full length mural shot and creation video coming soon of this labor of love for my fam @tahoewellness 💙

Got down for day one of @bitcoin.conference yesterday, going explosive on this piece today will offer new challenges and I’ve got the solutions broadcasting through my mind’s eye. Though I started out doing Graffiti Art in the mid 80’s it’s now been some 27 years freestyling live so you can feel what it feels like with me. Art is nothing more than an idea brought into the real world with passion. #Bitcoin2023 DM for link to Scarce City #Bitcoin auction ✊🏼✊🏽✊🏾✊🏿

Brining back my man of ascension & the realization of good ideas based in the natural laws of the universe. The feeling of independence & free thought that good ideas bring in a world of gangster bankers, ideas like #bitcoin liberate the soul & give knowledge of self. All parts contain the whole! Rise up & ascend, be the Revolution!!! #Bitcoin2023 more to come @bitcoin.conference ✊🏼✊🏽✊🏾✊🏿

Live Art is inspired by the environment as well the current state of mind one rests in. I enjoy painting among open-minded individuals who share some base of knowledge. The Bitcoin community is something special, it feels like a lone saloon on the last frontier full of revolutionaries & outlaws, a counter-culture composed of independent & free-thinking minds. I have found a wellspring of information & inspiration over the past 3 years coming out to the @bitcoin.conference in Miami. This incredible diverse audience has been embracing my work & narrative, bringing me some much needed perspective & hope during these despotic times. The shared realization is a powerful feeling & this piece expresses my sentiment of being in a slightly anarchic state of voluntaryism while above all being free. Here is the final shot of 11 hrs smacking paint down alongside great conversations. The ascension continues in my narrative as a visual metaphor, depicting the feeling of acceleration infused with the force of attraction. Some people hit this moment high on DMT, while others get it when an idea finally clicks, the spark of life from where our joy & inspiration generate. The future, the past, all visible from this state of consciousness. “Traveling without Moving,” 2023, 4x5’ acrylic on canvas. #Bitcoin2023

Peep Game 👀 After-hours tour last month with the founders of @museumofgraffiti new space right in the heart of Wynwood, Miami. What an experience for the art goer! The museum’s walls pay homage to defining innovators, moments & ideas in Graffiti Art, immersing you in the rich history & minds of us vandals. I was honored to see my tag representing LA on a world map of diverse hand styles!!! The largest & most original art movement of the late 20th/early 21st century, graffiti is the response to a world gone mad, energizing the spirit of its youth in urban city hoods with calls for freedom & revolution at a time when art had become dry & lost its purpose. This powerful inspiration continues to flow through me to this day, fueling my skepticism of the state, politics, and those who would try to control me, an allergic reaction to all the lies & bullshit, as well my curiosity into the suppressed knowledge of our hidden history. We got to hang & build with @alankets @a.l.l.i.s.o.n.f cooking up something epic for end of the year so stay tuned #earthpeople #graffitiart #museumofgraffiti ✊🏼✊🏽✊🏾✊🏿

Today marks the 30th anniversary of my dear brother #SK8ONE who was killed by an Amtrak train while hitting box cars in a rail yard doing what he loved. Graffiti was his passion, and to have died in action was crushing. His passing caused significant change in everyone’s life that knew him. It marked a major awakening in me that transformed forever how I felt about the world and the art I was creating. SK8 put me on to so much culture that resonates deep in this 50th year celebrating Hip-Hop. Life is so potent yet temporary, so many chase after fame & instant gratification to soothe the stresses of their soul, but they miss the point, which is to leave a mark & get on with it. Maybe it’s the materialist in us, or is it simply fear that drives the narcissist to believe they are more special than the rest? But even great egos will fade as the next generation redefines life for the masses. Today is one of those days that transcends normality, today marks the remembrance of a giant who more than left his mark, who changed many lives by being authentic & inspiring the rebel in us all. It is rare that an individual is recognized on such a scale outside of the official bs narrative. SKATE ONE is forever that timeless titan many strive to be, yet they lack the will power to be what he was, a natural born leader & mythical hero!!! Love you my brother, I see you in everything. ✊🏼✊🏽✊🏾✊🏿🙏

In my early twenties I was inspired by a book called “The Cipher Of Genesis” by Carlo Suares. Written in the early 20th century, it is a reinterpretation of the creation story through the Ha-Qabala, bringing logic & reason into an electromagnetic view of reality’s cause & effect. @teacha_krsone & his song “Why Is That” was paralleling my studies at the time, helping form this vision of a modern day tale we all see unfolding in our cities; forgotten souls resurrected from skid row, a prophet of untold fortune cometh. The poem I wrote was beautifully embellished on the tablets by master sensei @chaz_bojorquez we did several collaborations in the mid to late 90’s. This piece proudly hangs in the collection of @thundercatmusic ⚡️⚡️⚡️

With all the challenges humanity faces it’s empowering to see an LA OG out there representing the resistance to the #matrixmedia and their brainwashing psyop ✊🏼✊🏽✊🏾✊🏿 I painted you into #DestroyYourIllusions knowing that you would be playing an important role. PEACE, MEAR ONE CBS WCA #cubefanart

Never before had my inner compass spoken so loud to me than during the lockdown. I quickly recognized the necessity to pay attention to the details, especially the ones the nightly news wasn’t mentioning. Through all the media circus I learned to trust my feelings, helping me to rethink the official narrative in order to protect against an obvious threat. Dr. Rashid Buttar was one of the first voices I discovered early on who offered a wealth of comparative medical knowledge contrary to the illogical fear propaganda being thrown around by Big Pharma profiteers. It was a very dangerous time for an independent to come out with the research they were exposing, but Dr. Buttar took a firm stand, becoming very outspoken when we needed medical professionals to be brave. For 3 years Buttar & what the #matrixmedia dubbed “the disinformation dozen” were heavily criticized & mocked for being conspiracy theorists. But of course now we see the real data coming out on #gainoffunctionresearch #bioweapons & C19 vaccine efficacy confirming many of their claims. Back in February of this year Dr. Buttar’s health had begun rapidly deteriorating, and on May 18th he passed away with much confusion & shock as to the cause of his death. With respect to his stance against Big Pharma & the WHO, & according to those close to him, foul play cannot be ruled out. It is chilling to watch the interview he gave just days before his tragic death believing himself to have been poisoned. Dr. Buttar was a loving husband, father, retired Major in the U.S. Army, committed to continually questioning the official narrative & exposing a world misled by the powerful & a future full of despotic decay. This board game is very real and he is a light warrior among many who risk all to inform the public of the lies & greed that plagues the world. R.I.P. #drrashidbuttar #lightwarrior #destroyyourillusions

For nearly 4 decades Dr. Anthony Fauci served as Director of the U.S. National Institute of Allergy & Infectious Diseases, but since 9/11 I argue has been moonlighting as a leading weapons manufacturer for the United States government. Hear me out. In 2002 Bush appointed Fauci to lead the multibillion dollar US biodefense program called “Project Bioshield,” which was funded in large part by post-9/11 Patriot Act taxpayer monies. With his coffers overflowing he was able to set up at least 18 different biomedical research facilities focusing on the flu, SARS-CoV-2 & MERS virus & vaccines. However in 2014 due to pressure from hundreds of scientists to shut them down after 3 reported bug leaks, Obama issued a moratorium on all lab operations. So Fauci moved them offshore to, you guessed it, Wuhan. Simon Wain-Hobson, then chairman of the nonprofit Foundation for Vaccine Research, stated in an editorial in the journal Nature “[Obama’s moratorium] was strictly for public relations," as billions more continued to pour into Fauci’s “Project Bioshield” activities at the Wuhan Institute of Virology where both the FBI & the Department of Energy have now concluded the coronavirus originated. Fast forward to October 2019 when the coronavirus pandemic exercise was presented to world leaders in Geneva at Event 201 co-hosted by the WEF & none other than the puppet master of eugenics himself, Bill Gates. They ran simulations on everything from bioweapons lab leaks to treatment & even media censorship cover ups. And the rest is history. So what really is the Great Reset all about? And can Agenda 2030 truly be a depopulation agenda? Follow the money … (cont.👇)

Inside this closed environment exists a reality unleashed when hatched; concentric layers undulate from nothingness revealing the perpetual cycles of birth & death. That which is forms from what was within, signifying how every part contains the whole as a living practice in thinking. An awareness of cause & effect was bestowed upon the ancients who engaged life rigorously in order to experience direct connection with the universal energies. In this primordial vision I paint one of our earliest God constructs, the serpent, mythologized as a symbol of knowledge. This same deity appears in Genesis as well many other serpent worshiping cultures around the world such as the Naga. It is often times seen taking on the form of a feathered serpent, like the dragon in ancient Chinese lore & Kukulkan/Quetzalcoatl as it is known to the Aztecs depicted throughout their stone temples & rock art carvings. Vedic teachings recognize this symbol as the Kundalini energy running through our spinal cord up into our brains tying our limbic system into the vast electromagnetic field of consciousness, while ancient Egyptian hieroglyphs in Dendera portray the serpent more literally as electricity itself. The fact that both Pharaohs & Shiva were so often depicted accompanied by this half-divine creature is more than just coincidence. Whether it is a 200k year old tale as told by the Vedas or 4.5 billion years old as some believe, the Cosmic Egg & Serpent is nonetheless a shared myth so ancient its become source, transcending time itself. Deep within there is gnosis waiting to be discovered. #cosmicegg #metaphysicalsurrealism

social_posts.post_text: Everything echoes from this primordial state of love. Not no hippy dippy love, but the love that derives all consciousness. Heat is a phenomenon in a cold universe. Back when I started vandalizing the city of LA it was my dream to be accepted & respected. I think all us Hip Hop Gen Xers wanted that. To perfect the tradition & cultivate the culture. I evolved my graffiti from a Wild Style during my pioneering days. We were a rugged bunch, a bit of tunnel vision at first, like an army, my peers & I criticized anyone who stepped out of bounds i.e. anything other than freehand spray paint, so no bucket paint, no rollers, no stencils. Thankfully we all grew from each other. Big ups to the innovators @futuradosmil @mode2official @riskrock @og_slick @hextgo #charliedtk PJ of WCA #mistone as well the master painters @robertwilliamsartist @alexgreycosm who inspired & challenged my own graffiti boundaries to discover a more freestyle technique. With the living soundtrack of @freestylefellowship I was learning to develop my passions & head for foreign territory intellectually. 

My graffiti became so outside the box I decided to explore painting in acrylic & oil brush. In my studio I elevated through experimenting with psychedelics in a total vision quest while studying the great metaphysical minds like Carl Jung, Manly P. Hall, Aldous Huxley, books from the late 19th century delving into the occult, gnosticism, astrology, yoga & the tarot teachings. These experiences instruct my paintings away from the bourgeois, rather an outlaw outlier high plains drifter mode of creating from this state of revolution & spiritual liberation for all humanity. 

Graffiti taught me how to refine my rebellion to authority, to make it beautiful as well articulate the important details some might miss. The excitingly explosive & destructive nature of vandalism is in contrast to its higher component, the visionary communicative art that arises from those who awaken through resistance to a non-creative system. The process of developing & learning as an autodidact has given me much heartache as well high-minded insight into the meaning of my imagination at the crossroads of critical thinking witnessed by a spiritual being experiencing real life. There is no escape out there, the only way out is within.

“Gett’n Away With It,” c.2000, oil.

As it was said, may you live in interesting times, and here we are. I’ve invested a great deal of thought & reflection into what it is to be conscious; using myth & philosophy I’m compiling a perspective on life many are unaware of. Hang these visions in your home as a psychic magnet for higher conversation. Share yourself & thoughts with others drenched in the logos of antiquity as well the unheard voices of the future. This gnosis is ready for all who are willing to open their minds to the depths of our being. I hope these works bring inspiration, liberation & a sense of meaning alternative to that which is taught by the system.

I’m thrilled to announce that my biggest solo show in nearly a decade will debut at the @museumofgraffiti during @artbasel Miami! 

On December 6th take a deep dive with me into the suppressed knowledge & global mythologies of our past. Things are not what they seem, especially our story of who we are. As a lifetime autodidact I decided to set out on a journey these past five years throughout North America's Southwest, Great Basin deserts & plateaus to explore the mythos in our own backyard as told through archaic rock wall art & architecture. My field research has uncovered thousands of petroglyphs, pictographs, as well ruins & other trace markings of a world I had no idea existed & of a history we know very little about. 

For me graffiti has always been about resisting authority, how vandalism is telling a story, an adventure, hieroglyphic evidence of the dissatisfied soul. So what do these ancient forms of graffiti have to say? What is the God mythos depicted in rock art & literature throughout all antiquity? How did this so-called interplanetary war of the Gods take place? The Ancient Greeks write about a great reordering in our solar system's hierarchy; the pre-dynastic Chinese depict dragons in the heavens, interpreted by some as comets that brought great cataclysm; the Sumerians share similar tales of a pantheon of Gods who descended to earth & were destroyed by a great flood; Native & Meso-American tribes leave behind sky God legends carved in stone in the form of petroglyphs & pictographs, the original forms of graffiti.

Stories from these ancient cultures line up with evidence found in the #YoungerDryas hypothesis of 12,000 years ago - civilizations cycling through different times of destruction & rebirth, landscapes once inhabited by red-haired giants & shaped by a continual re-terraformation of our world with thunderbolts from the skies wiping out megalithic cultures as told in the Great Flood of Atlantis, now considered by many to be more than just myth. 

But all of this information remains hidden as if it were taboo, a conspiracy I hope to shed light upon in my newest body of work called #MetaphysicalSurrealism. Ticket link in my bio 🪬
Shoutout @juxtapozmag for the show highlight ✊🏼✊🏽✊🏾✊🏿 “Metaphysical Surrealism” opens Dec.6th @museumofgraffiti ticket link on my page. #mearone #metaphysicalsurrealism

Early 20th century catastrophe theorist Immanuel Velikovsky stated we were once in a polar configuration with Saturn for a time called the #PurpleDawn when suddenly our solar system came into a cataclysmic re-settling run in with the sun & Jupiter’s binary system. We recall here the myths of Saturn castrating his father Uranus only to be over powered by Jupiter ending with our current heliocentric system. Ancient Sumerian, Persian, Egyptian, Greek & Indo Aryan cultures, the Mayan natives of Mexico as well the Inca, all speak of a war of the gods in the sky that took place & a great deluge that was to follow. Remnants of this #GreatFlood covered every ancient site on this planet up until the early 19th century when we began to excavate these ruins & open them up for tourism. This cataclysmic occurrence may be the reason why Chaldean astrologers created the zodiacal calendar hoping to predict the future so they might be prepared when the cycles of time repeated itself bringing disaster for the unprepared. Global coherence in the mythical great flood & astronomical cataclysmic events exist in literature, scripture, sacred books, petroglyphs, pictographs, sculptures, architecture & frescoes including early renaissance works record all of these scenarios in great detail. From a world that was supposedly unconnected, everyone seems to share the same story. Thus, in the spirit of the master paintings of the Fall of Rome & Egypt to the great western exploration depictions of our prehistoric origin I seek to vandalize the psyche, repainting my version of new found ancient gnosis into the art vernacular. #SquatterMan #YoungerDryas #MetaphysicalSurrealism (Tile 5/6)

The institutions of knowledge would have us believe that hundreds of millions of years of erosion created the world we see today, yet don’t take into consideration the singular topographical continuity we find in places like America’s southwest & Great Basin. Littered throughout these deserts & plateaus are melted rocks frozen in time as if they once oozed across the earth’s surface like hot wax. Some catastrophist theorists suggest that the geometrical continuity of the landscape & conformity in rock formation repeating itself over great distances were caused by an EM (electromagnetic) apocalypse. Los Alamos Laboratory nuclear scientist Dr. Anthony Peratt first compared the petroglyphs found in these regions to high energy sky events that were taking place in the heavens producing brilliant plasma phenomena like red sprites & auroras. The Squatter Man, i.e. the God Self Icon, is a perfect example of such symbols in an alien sky created by an EM discharge brought on from a number of overlapping events like solar nova, comet & meteorite interactions releasing high energy field perturbations in the millions of degrees, planetary displacement & solar rearrangement. The Electric Universe Model proposed by @thethunderboltsproject aims to address this crisis in cosmology by bridging the lack of connectivity in traditional theory with research-based evidence in laboratory experiments echoed in our mythological records. This is but one in many new paintings I’m creating in the hopes of rediscovering who we are from an alternative perspective, encrypted as a kind of rubics cube existing in different configurations in continuity with the potentials existing in these laws of nature. #PerattInstability #SquatterMan #YoungerDryas #MetaphysicalSurrealism (Tile 6/6)

There was a time we were completely free, once children of Gaia & her subtle energies. The wind carried language, communication was instant, no words but direct universal gnosis. Psychic bridging was shared around the world, all one family applying the laws of nature to find purpose with a spiritual life in a physical world. The sky was our calendar, food was abundant & love our unified sense of being. Fear did not exist because truth extended beyond our material bodies undulating along a magnetic direction allowing fluidity in daily travel, completely aware of our past & future lives because time had no meaning. Doing the work of the Gods, feeding ourselves their gifts found in the psychedelic fungi & mineral deposits informing us of a universal broadcast from the divine consciousness of the fractal mind. 

We all share these mythological roots as well historical amnesia about this Golden Age. Diverse archetypes in our self & ego express themselves powerfully in our subconscious moment to moment such as Fear & Love derived from our separation with source. Those born of fear took opportunity after cyclical catastrophes meant to evolve humanity, yet chose to manipulate the minds of many subjugating any resistance. Religion, the human desire to communicate directly with Nature, God, the Universe was co-opted & no longer could rightfully express itself without risk of persecution. Science, the thirst to question reality & challenge the status quo in search of imperiled truth was overcome by the influence of fear & like a disease its poison spread so as to obfuscate the cycles. 

But there is nothing you cannot know, so we search the darkest void for a force that even the weight of emptiness cannot suppress, a spark of light igniting into a greater manifestation. Light penetrates all dark & we must know it too. This piece was my search to know all the love & light that ever was, is & could be. Gaia’s truth is awaiting your awakening as we are all one movement in this future primitive flow state of bliss & timeless space. “The Golden Age of Gaia” 5x7’ acrylic on canvas, on view until 2.5.24 @museumofgraffiti #MetaphysicalSurrealism
